==English==
===Etymology===
Old English ''[[sealt]]'', from Germanic, from Indo-European.  Cognate with Dutch ''[[zout]]'', German ''[[Salz]]'', Swedish ''[[#Swedish|salt]]''; and with Greek ''[[ἅλς]]'', Latin ''[[sal]]'', Welsh ''[[halen]]'', Russian ''[[соль]]''.

